<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880930-0159 </DOCNO><HL> Avery Net Rose 34% On 4% Sales Increase In Its Third Quarter </HL><SO> </SO><CO> AVY </CO><IN> ERN </IN><DATELINE> PASADENA, Calif.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Avery International Corp. reported 34% higher net income for its third quarter ended Aug. 31, on a 4% increase in sales.    Profit rose to $17.1 million, or 39 cents a share, from $12.8 million, or 29 cents a share. Sales climbed to $382 million, from $367 million last year.    &quot;Strong performances from the company's core businesses, particularly the Materials and the Specialty Tapes operations in the U.S. and Europe, contributed to the third consecutive quarter of record sales and profits in 1988,&quot; Charles D. Miller, the company's chairman.    For the first nine months, net rose to $56.6 million, or $1.29 a share, up from $41.7 million, or 99 cents a share, the year earlier. Sales rose to $1.17 billion from $1.08 billion.    Avery makes adhesives, labels, tapes, office products and specialty chemicals. Shares of Avery, which said it has about 11,000 employees world-wide, closed yesterday at $22.875 a share, up $1.125, in composite trading on the New York Stock Exchange. </TEXT></DOC>